The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Orissa trounce Meghalaya 4-1

Thiruvananthapuram: Orissa powered to a 4-1 win over Meghalaya for their second win in the four-team cluster III of the Santosh Trophy National Football Championship at the Chandrasekharan Nair Stadium here on Sunday. 

Gyana Ranjan Samal drew first blood for Orissa in the second minute while Rajendra Prasad Singh bolstered the lead in the 24th minute off a pass from Rupayi Handsdah. Samal then made it to 3-0 through another strike in the 38th minute. 

At the breather Orissa were leading 3-0. 

Meghalaya then made some good moves and in the 46th minute Rogesterwell Basaiwmdit reduced the margin (1-3) converting a pass from Pynskhem Garod on the right wing. Samal consolidated Orissas lead with another goal, his third. 

In the morning, in the three-team cluster II, Himachal Pradesh lost their second match and bowed out of the tournament. Bihar beat Himchal 3-0. 

Assam beat Chhattisgarh 10-1 in another preliminary round match in Kozhikode. 

Chhattisgarh had lost to Railways in the opening encounter. Now it will be a direct fight between Railways and Assam when they meet on Tuesday to qualify for the next round. 

Earlier, Railways thrashed Pondicherry 8-0 while Uttar Pradesh beat Uttaranchal 2-0. 

 (PTI) 




